description: Knew of the plot to burn Kyoto to the ground. Captured and tortured _very_ slowly by Hijikata.
Takeda Sokaku, native of Aizu and head of Daito-ryu Aikijutsu. Witnessed the Battle of Aizu as a child.
Never before seen picture of Matsudaira Katamori. It truly shows how young he was in those days.
Bakufu senior counselor, and successor to Abe Masahiro.
Led the Choshuu meeting at the Ikeda-ya, July 6th, 1864.
Head of the defenders of Nagaoka Castle, summer 1868.
Was possibly in the Shinsengumi. Not quite sure.
Friend of Kondou from Hino (in what is now Tokyo).
General of the armies of Nagaoka. Beheaded in Aizu on September 9, 1868.
Administrator of Nagaoka immediately after the Boshin war. Known for the ";100 sacks of rice"; story-- sold rice given to Nagaoka by a neighboring domain, in order to fund construction of a school.
